		<main id="main" class="site-main" role="main"><article id="post-30" class="post-30 page type-page status-publish hentry"><header class="entry-header"><h1 class="entry-title">A Message from Scott W. Lay</h1>	</header><!-- .entry-header --><div class="entry-content">
		<div><img width="200" height="300" class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-13009" alt="Picture of Superintendent Scott W. Lay" src="https://nevco.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Scott-3-8-17-Bio-Pix-200x300.jpg" srcset="https://nevco.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Scott-3-8-17-Bio-Pix-200x300.jpg 200w, https://nevco.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Scott-3-8-17-Bio-Pix-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://nevco.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Scott-3-8-17-Bio-Pix-683x1024.jpg 683w, https://nevco.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Scott-3-8-17-Bio-Pix.jpg 1783w" sizes="(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px"></div>
<p>Welcome to the Nevada County Superintendent of Schools!</p>
<p>I’m honored to be your Nevada County Superintendent of Schools.  Our office takes pride in providing educational, financial, and student support programs for almost 12,000 students in Nevada County.  We work closely with the county’s nine school districts and seven charter schools, with a total of over 30 schools between them, to support all students and educators.</p>
<p>I hope you find our website to be a useful tool in discovering what our office has to offer students, parents, community members and educators.  For a list of the various programs and services we offer, go to: <a href="https://nevco.org/programs-services/">NCSOS Programs &amp; Services</a>.  We also partner with a number of community businesses and non-profits on a variety of programs, all with the goal of providing the best programs for our students.</p>
<p><strong><img width="300" height="56" class="alignleft wp-image-14190 size-medium" alt="Scott W. Lay's Signature" src="https://nevco.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/Scotts-Signature-and-Title-300x56.png" srcset="https://nevco.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/Scotts-Signature-and-Title-300x56.png 300w, https://nevco.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/Scotts-Signature-and-Title.png 317w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px"></strong></p>
<p> </p>
<p> </p>
<hr>
<div><a href="https://nevco.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Coronavirus-Letter-from-Scott-W.-Lay-3-5-20.pdf"><img width="300" height="167" class="wp-image-20671 size-medium alignleft" alt="" src="https://nevco.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/coronavirus-image-300x167.jpg" srcset="https://nevco.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/coronavirus-image-300x167.jpg 300w, https://nevco.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/coronavirus-image.jpg 525w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px"></a></div>
<p>Public, charter and private schools, along with the Nevada County Superintendent of Schools Office (NCSOS) are teaming up with Nevada County Public Health Department to provide students, families and the public with the most accurate information available regarding the 2019 Novel Coronavirus (COVID-19) situation in Nevada County.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><span style="color: #ff0000;"><strong>Update 7</strong></span> April 2, 2020 – <a href="https://nevco.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/NEVADA-COUNTY-PUBLIC-SCHOOLS-ADVISORY-5-COVID-19-4.2.20.pdf">Nevada County Public Schools Advisory Letter from Superintendent Scott W. Lay #5.  </a></p>
<p><a href="https://nevco.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/COMUNICADO-5-DE-LAS-ESCUELAS-PUBLICAS-DEL-CONDADO-DE-NEVADA-CON-REFERENCIA-AL-COVID-19-4-2-2020.pdf">Español Comunicado #5 De Las Escuelas Publicas Del Condado de Nevada Actualización sobre el Coronavirus. </a></p>
<p><span style="color: #ff0000;"><strong>Update 6 </strong></span>March 30, 2020 – <a href="https://nevco.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Message-to-Community-Mental-Health-Resources-3-30-20-Update-6-1.pdf">Message to the Community regarding mental health resources from Superintendent Scott W. Lay</a></p>
<p><span style="color: #ff0000;"><strong>Update</strong> <strong>5</strong></span> March 27, 2020 – <a href="https://nevco.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/NEVADA-COUNTY-PUBLIC-SCHOOLS-ADVISORY-4-COVID-19-3.27.20.pdf">Nevada County Public Schools Advisory Letter from Superintendent Scott W. Lay #4</a></p>
<p><strong><span style="color: #ff0000;">Update 4</span></strong> March 19, 2020 – <a href="https://nevco.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Nevada-County-Public-Schools-Advisory-3-3-19-20.pdf">Nevada County Public Schools Advisory Letter from Superintendent Scott W. Lay #3 </a></p>
<p><strong><span style="color: #ff0000;">Update 3</span></strong> March 16, 2020 – <a href="https://nevco.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Navada-County-Schools-Advisory.pdf">Nevada County Public Schools Advisory Letter from Superintendent Scott W. Lay </a></p>
<p><span style="color: #ff0000;"><strong>Update 2</strong> </span>March 12, 2020 – <a href="https://nevco.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Letter-to-families-COVID-19-3.12.20.pdf">Letter to families from Superintendent Scott W. Lay</a></p>
<p><span style="color: #ff0000;"><strong>Update 1</strong></span> March 6, 2020 – Please see an important <a href="https://nevco.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Coronavirus-Guidance-Letter-3-5-2020.pdf">Coronavirus Guidance Letter</a> from our California State Superintendent of Public Instruction, Tony Thurmond.</p>
<p><a href="https://nevco.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Coronavirus-Letter-from-Scott-W.-Lay-3-5-20.pdf">Coronavirus Letter from Superintendent Scott W. Lay</a></p>
<p>Download <a href="https://nevco.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Instructions-for-parents.pdf">Instructions for parents</a> and <a href="https://nevco.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Tips-for-Parents.pdf">Tips for Parents</a></p>
<p><a href="https://www.mynevadacounty.com/2924/Coronavirus">Coronavirus Information from Nevada County Public Health </a></p>
<p><a href="https://211connectingpoint.org/category/nevada-county/">Contact 211 for further information</a></p>
<div><a href="https://211connectingpoint.org/category/nevada-county/"><img width="210" height="116" class="alignnone wp-image-20758" alt="" src="https://nevco.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/211.jpg"></a></div>
<hr style="clear: both; color: #333333; cursor: default; font-family: Georgia,&amp;quot; times new roman&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;bitstream charter&amp;quot;,times,serif; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; margin-bottom: 25px; orphans: 2; text-align: center; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">
<div><a style="color: #0066cc;" href="https://nevco.org/school-lunch-program-guidelines-2019-2020/?highlight=school%20lunch%20program"><img width="300" height="157" class="size-full wp-image-20915 alignleft" style="border-image-outset: 0; border-image-repeat: stretch; border-image-slice: 100%; border-image-source: none; border-image-width: 1; float: left; height: auto; max-width: 50%; margin: 0px 25px 25px 0px; border: medium none currentColor;" alt="" src="https://nevco.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/free-and-reduced-lunch-logo-300x157-1.png"></a></div>
<p style="color: #333333; font-family: Georgia,&amp;quot; times new roman&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;bitstream charter&amp;quot;,times,serif; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;"><a href="https://nevco.org/school-lunch-program-guidelines-2019-2020/?highlight=school%20lunch%20program">Free and Reduced Lunch Program COVID-19 updated guidelines.</a></p>
<p style="color: #333333; font-family: Georgia,&amp;quot; times new roman&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;bitstream charter&amp;quot;,times,serif; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">Effective March 27, 2020 The United States Department of Agriculture (USDA) approved a nationwide waiver to support access to meals for children while minimizing potential exposure to COVID-19.</p>
<hr style="clear: both; color: #333333; cursor: default; font-family: Georgia,&amp;quot; times new roman&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;bitstream charter&amp;quot;,times,serif; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; margin-bottom: 25px; orphans: 2; text-align: center; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">
<h3 style="color: #006633; font-family: Georgia,&amp;quot; times new roman&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;bitstream charter&amp;quot;,times,serif; font-size: 18px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">
<a style="color: #0066cc;" href="https://nevco.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/CANCELLED-JOB-FAIR-POSTER-3.jpg"><img width="1" height="1" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-20766" style="border-image-outset: 0; border-image-repeat: stretch; border-image-slice: 100%; border-image-source: none; border-image-width: 1; display: block; height: auto; max-width: 100%; margin: 0px; border: medium none currentColor;" alt="" src="https://nevco.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/CANCELLED-JOB-FAIR-POSTER-3.jpg"></a><a href="https://sites.google.com/nevco.org/distancelearning-classroom/welcome"><img width="300" height="142" class="wp-image-20908 size-medium alignleft" style="border-image-outset: 0; border-image-repeat: stretch; border-image-slice: 100%; border-image-source: none; border-image-width: 1; float: left; height: auto; max-width: 50%; margin: 0px 25px 25px 0px; border: medium none currentColor;" alt="" src="https://nevco.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/distance-learning--300x142.png" srcset="https://nevco.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/distance-learning--300x142.png 300w, https://nevco.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/distance-learning-.png 750w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px"></a><b></b><strong>Attention Educators and Parents</strong>
</h3>
<p style="color: #333333; font-family: Georgia,&amp;quot; times new roman&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;bitstream charter&amp;quot;,times,serif; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;" dir="ltr">During this period of school closures, Nevada County Superintendent of Schools Office and local schools are committed to supporting continued learning for our students and community through our Distance Learning Resource Link. To view this resource go to:  <a id="LPlnk557483" style="color: #0066cc;" href="https://sites.google.com/nevco.org/distancelearning-classroom/welcome" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" data-auth="NotApplicable">https://sites.google.com/nevco.org/distancelearning-classroom/welcome</a></p>
<p style="color: #333333; font-family: Georgia,&amp;quot; times new roman&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;bitstream charter&amp;quot;,times,serif; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;" dir="ltr">NCSoS is grateful to our educators and community for their contributions to this resource. To share additional learning links or distance learning resources please contact Andrea Marks at <a style="color: #0066cc;" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" data-auth="NotApplicable">amarks@nevco.org</a>. <b></b><i></i><u></u></p>
<hr>
<div><img width="300" height="241" class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-20021" alt="Career Pathway Partners Logo" src="https://nevco.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Career-Pathway-Partners-Logo-300x241.jpg" srcset="https://nevco.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Career-Pathway-Partners-Logo-300x241.jpg 300w, https://nevco.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Career-Pathway-Partners-Logo-768x617.jpg 768w, https://nevco.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Career-Pathway-Partners-Logo.jpg 775w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px"></div>
<p>Check out our newly launched program Career Pathway Partners. We are populating a directory with businesses and volunteers who would like to come to schools as a guest speaker, offer workplace tours or job shadowing, mentor students and at the highest level of participation, host student interns. We are anticipating that this database will offer a sufficient number of registered businesses and volunteers to share with school teachers, staff and administrators by this spring. To get involved, encourage local businesses to register at <a href="https://nevco.org/cpp/">https://nevco.org/cpp/</a></p>
<p><iframe width="640" height="360" title="vimeo-player" src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/383334522" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"></iframe></p>
